snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks for bringing tears in my eyes, Coke studio :'( . Mesmerizing performance.. ! I've heard it 10 minutes ago and my arm hair are still straight up ! I've got goosebumps... Rest in peace our dear muted flute ! ... I've recalled a poem by P.B Shelly.

Music, when soft voices die, 
Vibrates in the memory
Odours, when sweet violets sicken, 
Live within the sense they quicken. 

Rose leaves, when the rose is dead, 
Are heaped for the belovèd's bed; 
And so thy thoughts, when thou art gone, 
Love itself shall slumber on. 

Rest in peace the sound of love ! no one can snatch your voice from us :') Thanks Coke Studio !

snippet.textDisplay:
Standing ovation for those who manage to turn the praising into a hate speech
MQM, TTP, who ever did this, the point is that Amjad Sabri is no more with us. Please stop blaming THIS or THAT for Sabri's sad demise. Instead, BE THE CHANGE we need and that is tolerance towards our differences.
Try to eradicate EXTREMISM by opening yourself to the fact that everyone has that the right to believe what he/she thinks is right. So, instead of CORRECTING them, learn to live in peace with these differences.
We are the ones who vote for the parties which after winning try to squeeze last drop of our blood for their worldly luxuries. So, vote sensibly. Stop blaming the SYSTEM, it is US who make the SYSTEM.
Blaming and condemnation will do no good. It will not bring victims of extremism, terrorism, political rivalry back. But if we start acting (which we don't) we can stop more people from falling victims of such atrocities.
And also a lot of artists have put their day and night into bringing this beautiful season 9 to us. At the least, please say some good words for them instead of making this comment section look like a typical talk show.
